Process called "emit_jmp" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    If operand1 is not 0:
        Note: Target the block label in the CURRENT function's namespace. The
        Note: discriminator at ctx offset 56 is the same one emit_basic_block used
        Note: for this function, so the jump resolves to .LBB<func_idx>_<target_id>.
        Let func_idx be __load(ctx, 56)
        Let target_id be __load(operand1, 16)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tjmp\t.LBB")
        Let func_idx_str be StringUtils.integer_to_string(func_idx)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, func_idx_str)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "_")
        Let id_str be StringUtils.integer_to_string(target_id)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, id_str)
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_conditional_jmp" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer, mnemonic as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    If operand1 is not 0:
        Note: Target the block label in the CURRENT function's namespace using the
        Note: same discriminator (ctx offset 56) emit_basic_block used, resolving to
        Note: .LBB<func_idx>_<target_id>.
        Let func_idx be __load(ctx, 56)
        Let target_id be __load(operand1, 16)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\t")
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, mnemonic)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\t.LBB")
        Let func_idx_str be StringUtils.integer_to_string(func_idx)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, func_idx_str)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "_")
        Let id_str be StringUtils.integer_to_string(target_id)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, id_str)
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_call" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Emits the x86_64 SysV machine instruction sequence for a LIR call,
    dispatching the call symbol based on the LIR call's recorded calling
    convention (offset 64). Per CEO Q3 amendment, objc-convention calls
    are routed through _objc_msgSend@PLT; the parser already wrote the
    Runa-side method-name identifier into the AST and the HIR/MIR/LIR
    chain propagated it to the LIR call's operand-1 callee_name slot,
    but for objc dispatch the symbol is replaced with the Objective-C
    runtime entry point at codegen time. Receiver and selector argument
    marshaling (rdi for `self`, rsi for `_cmd`) is performed earlier by
    lower_call's SysV register assignment.

    Convention dispatch table:
      0 (c) / 1 (stdcall) / 2 (fastcall) / 3 (cdecl): standard
        callq <callee_name>.
      4 (syscall): the callee_name is the runtime syscall thunk for the
        target arch (e.g., `syscall_write`); a standard callq emits the
        right instruction since the thunk applies the syscall calling
        convention internally.
      5 (objc): emits `callq _objc_msgSend@PLT`. Non-Darwin targets are
        rejected at link time by linker_driver_emit_objc_rejection.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Reads operand1 (offset 16 of the LIR call instruction) to find the
    LIRValue whose offset-16 field carries the callee_name string. Reads
    the calling_convention (offset 64) to choose the emission path.

    Two distinct paths:
      objc (convention_id == 5): emits the literal `\tcallq\t_objc_msgSend@PLT`
        directive followed by a newline. The Runa-side method identifier
        is intentionally discarded -- it is encoded as the selector in
        rsi prior to the call site.
      default: emits `\tcallq\t<callee_name>` followed by a newline,
        where <callee_name> is the alias symbol (set by the External
        declaration's `as "..."` clause, or the bare process name when
        omitted). The label `\tcallq\t` is the GNU as syntax for a
        64-bit relative-PLT call.

    Failure modes: a null callee_name or null operand1 causes the
    Process to silently skip emission, which would yield a malformed
    text section but should not crash; upstream LIR construction
    guarantees both fields are populated for non-indirect calls.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1). One pointer load (output stream), two field loads from the
    instruction, one conditional branch, two string emits. Total
    overhead is dominated by the asm_emit calls (~50 nanoseconds per
    call). Called once per LIR call instruction; cumulative cost
    proportional to call-site count in the program.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    The emitted text is consumed by an external assembler (`as`) which
    is the security boundary; this Process emits well-formed GNU as
    syntax with no user-controlled data interpolated except the
    alias_name from the External declaration. Aliases pass through
    parser validation that restricts them to identifier-shaped strings,
    so they cannot inject GAS directives or shell metacharacters. The
    objc path emits a fixed literal symbol (`_objc_msgSend@PLT`) with
    no user input on the codepath at all.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    Let convention_id be __load(instr, 64)
    Note: Sep-comp stage 4: @PLT cross-object flag (LIR call instruction offset 72),
    Note: threaded from the MIR call's cross_module flag by lower_call. When set, the
    Note: callee is a separately-compiled definition whose label is module-mangled, so
    Note: the call must go through the PLT: emit `callq <symbol>@PLT`. callee_name is
    Note: already the mangled symbol (the resolve pass put it on the MIR/LIR callee), so
    Note: caller and callee labels agree.
    Let cross_module be __load(instr, 72)

    If operand1 is not 0:
        Let callee_name be __load(operand1, 16)
        If callee_name is not 0:
            Note:
            Memory intrinsics __load/__store/__load8/__store8 are not real
            functions — they are direct memory accesses that the monolith
            desugars at parse time. In this separately-compiled pipeline they
            reach codegen as ordinary calls whose callee symbol is the bare
            intrinsic name (no definition exists, so the sepcomp resolver
            leaves the name unmangled). Inline them here as the equivalent
            base+index mov so no external symbol is required and the access is
            import-independent. SysV argument marshaling in lower_call has
            already placed arg0 (pointer) in %rdi, arg1 (byte offset) in %rsi,
            and arg2 (value, stores only) in %rdx; for loads the result is left
            in %rax (the SysV return register) so the post-call result move
            emitted by lower_call copies it into the destination register.
            __load/__store are 8-byte; __load8 zero-extends a byte into the
            full register; __store8 writes the low byte.
            :End Note
            If StringCore.string_equals(callee_name, "__load") is equal to 1:
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tmovq\t(%rdi,%rsi), %rax")
                Return 1
            End If
            If StringCore.string_equals(callee_name, "__load8") is equal to 1:
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tmovzbq\t(%rdi,%rsi), %rax")
                Return 1
            End If
            If StringCore.string_equals(callee_name, "__store") is equal to 1:
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tmovq\t%rdx, (%rdi,%rsi)")
                Return 1
            End If
            If StringCore.string_equals(callee_name, "__store8") is equal to 1:
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tmovb\t%dl, (%rdi,%rsi)")
                Return 1
            End If
            If convention_id is 5:
                Note: Q3 — Objective-C convention: emit objc_msgSend dispatch.
                Note: Selector arg-2 is already in rsi per SysV argument-marshal
                Note: in lower_call. The Runa-side name (e.g., "doSomething") is
                Note: dropped in favor of the dispatcher symbol.
                MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tcallq\t_objc_msgSend@PLT")
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "")
            Otherwise:
                If cross_module is not 0:
                    Note: Cross-object call to a module-mangled definition — route via PLT.
                    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tcallq\t")
                    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, callee_name)
                    MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "@PLT")
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Default path — direct call to the recorded symbol name.
                    Note: For convention syscall, the callee_name is itself a thunk
                    Note: function in primitives/assembly that wraps the syscall
                    Note: instruction; we emit the standard call to it.
                    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tcallq\t")
                    MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, callee_name)
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_call_indirect" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    If operand1 is not 0:
        Let reg_name be format_operand(operand1, 8)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\tcallq\t*")
        MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, reg_name)
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_ret" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lir_func be __load(ctx, 16)
    emit_epilogue(ctx, lir_func)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Memory and SSE Operations
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "emit_load_store" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer, suffix as Integer, is_load as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let section be MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT
    Let result be __load(instr, 8)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    Let operand2 be __load(instr, 24)

    Let size be 8
    If suffix is "b":
        Set size to 1
    End If
    If suffix is "w":
        Set size to 2
    End If
    If suffix is "l":
        Set size to 4
    End If

    If is_load is 1:
        Note: Load: mov mem, reg
        Let src_str be format_operand(operand1, size)
        Let dst_str be format_operand(result, size)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\tmov")
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, suffix)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\t")
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, src_str)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, ", ")
        MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, section, dst_str)
    Otherwise:
        Note: Store: mov reg, mem
        Set src_str to format_operand(operand2, size)
        Set dst_str to format_operand(operand1, size)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\tmov")
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, suffix)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\t")
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, src_str)
        MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, ", ")
        MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, section, dst_str)
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_sse_binary" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer, mnemonic as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let section be MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT
    Let result be __load(instr, 8)
    Let operand2 be __load(instr, 24)
    Let src_str be format_operand(operand2, 8)
    Let dst_str be format_operand(result, 8)

    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\t")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, mnemonic)
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\t")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, src_str)
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, ", ")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, section, dst_str)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_sse_unary" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer, mnemonic as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let section be MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT
    Let result be __load(instr, 8)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    Let src_str be format_operand(operand1, 8)
    Let dst_str be format_operand(result, 8)

    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\t")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, mnemonic)
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\t")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, src_str)
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, ", ")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, section, dst_str)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_cvt" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer, mnemonic as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let section be MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT
    Let result be __load(instr, 8)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    Let src_str be format_operand(operand1, 8)
    Let dst_str be format_operand(result, 8)

    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\t")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, mnemonic)
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, "\t")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, src_str)
    MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, section, ", ")
    MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, section, dst_str)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Special Instructions
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "emit_label_instr" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    If operand1 is not 0:
        Let label_name be __load(operand1, 16)
        If label_name is not 0:
            MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, label_name)
            MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, ":")
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_comment" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer returns Integer:
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    If operand1 is not 0:
        Let comment_text be __load(operand1, 16)
        If comment_text is not 0:
            MachineCode.asm_emit_to_section(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\t# ")
            MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, comment_text)
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "emit_inline_asm" that takes ctx as Integer, instr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Emit an inline-assembly block. The operand1 wrapper carries the dialect flag
    at offset 8 (0=intel default, 1=att) and the verbatim assembly text at
    offset 16. Intel-dialect bodies are wrapped with `.intel_syntax noprefix`
    before and `.att_syntax prefix` after, restoring the assembler's default
    AT&T mode for the surrounding compiler-generated code -- mirroring the
    monolith codegen (which emits these syntax-switch directives around every
    intel inline-asm body). AT&T-dialect bodies are emitted verbatim with no
    directives, since they are already in the assembler's default syntax.
    :End Note
    Let output be __load(ctx, 0)
    Let operand1 be __load(instr, 16)
    If operand1 is not 0:
        Let dialect be __load(operand1, 8)
        Let asm_text be __load(operand1, 16)
        If asm_text is not 0:
            If dialect is 1:
                Note: AT&T dialect: emit verbatim, no syntax-switch directives.
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, asm_text)
            Otherwise:
                Note: Intel dialect (default): bracket with syntax-switch directives.
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\t.intel_syntax noprefix")
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, asm_text)
                MachineCode.asm_emit_line(output, MachineCode.SECTION_TEXT, "\t.att_syntax prefix")
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process
